<body>
  <a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to content</a>
  <header class="site-head">
    <div class="site-head-inner">
      <a class="back" href="/">‹ <span>Home</span></a>
      <a href="/" aria-label="Black Swamp Totes home"><%- include("partials/cattail") %></a>
      <a class="call" href="tel:+14192622837" aria-label="Call Black Swamp Totes">Call</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container" id="main">
    <article class="legal" style="max-width:760px;margin:40px auto 64px;line-height:1.6;">
      <div class="eyebrow">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="display" style="font-size:clamp(34px,7vw,56px);margin:8px 0;">Rental Agreement &amp; Liability Waiver</h1>
      <p class="dim">Version <strong><%= termsVersion %></strong> · Effective <%= updated %></p>

      <p>This Rental Agreement and Liability Waiver (the “Agreement”) is between <strong>Black Swamp Totes</strong> (“BST,” “we,” “us”) and the person who books a rental (“you,” the “Renter”). By checking the “I have read and agree” box at booking, you accept this Agreement. We record that acceptance, the date and time, the version above, and your IP address. This Agreement applies alongside our <a href="/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Terms of Service</a>.</p>

      <h2>1. Equipment &amp; rental period</h2>
      <p>We rent you reusable moving bins and any related equipment (dollies) shown on your booking. The rental period begins when the bins are delivered (or picked up by you) and ends on the scheduled pickup (or return) date on your booking. If you need more time, extensions are billed at <span class="ph">[INSERT EXTENSION RATE — e.g. $0.30 per bin per day]</span> to the payment method on file.</p>

      <h2>2. Your responsibility for the bins while in your possession</h2>
      <p>From the moment the bins are delivered to you (or picked up by you) until they are returned to or retrieved by us, <strong>you are solely responsible for the bins and all equipment in your possession</strong>. You agree to keep them secure, use them only for their intended household-moving purpose, and not lend, sublet, sell, or allow them to leave your control. You bear the risk of loss, theft, or damage during this period regardless of cause.</p>

      <h2>3. Replacement cost for damaged or lost bins</h2>
      <p>Bins (and lids and dollies) must be returned in the same condition as delivered, ordinary wear excepted. For each bin or item that is <strong>lost, stolen, not returned, or returned damaged</strong> (including cracked or broken lids), you agree to pay a replacement charge of <span class="ph">[INSERT REPLACEMENT COST — e.g. $XX.00 per bin]</span> (and <span class="ph">[INSERT DOLLY REPLACEMENT COST — e.g. $XX.00 per dolly]</span>), charged to the payment method on file. You authorize that charge by accepting this Agreement.</p>

      <h2>4. Cleaning &amp; return condition</h2>
      <p>Bins must be returned <strong>empty and reasonably clean</strong>. Bins returned with trash, debris, liquids, hazardous materials, or significant contamination may incur a cleaning fee of up to <span class="ph">[INSERT CLEANING FEE — e.g. $XX.00]</span> per affected bin. The bins are for household moving only and may not be used for trash disposal, hazardous or flammable materials, liquids, or storage of prohibited items.</p>

      <h2>5. Late return</h2>
      <p>Bins must be available for pickup (or returned by you) on the scheduled date. Late returns are billed at <span class="ph">[INSERT LATE FEE — e.g. $XX.00 per day or the extension rate]</span> to the payment method on file until the bins are recovered. Bins not returned within <span class="ph">[INSERT WINDOW — e.g. 14 days]</span> of the scheduled pickup date may be treated as lost and charged at the replacement cost above.</p>

      <h2>6. Release of liability &amp; assumption of risk</h2>
      <p>You use the bins and equipment <strong>at your own risk</strong>. To the fullest extent permitted by law, <strong>Black Swamp Totes is not liable for any property damage, personal injury, or loss</strong> arising out of or relating to your use of the bins or equipment — including, without limitation, damage to your belongings, your home, vehicles, or any third party’s property, and injury to you or any other person — whether during loading, transport, unloading, storage, or any other use. The bins are provided <strong>“as is”</strong>; you are responsible for inspecting each bin before use and for not using any bin you believe to be unsafe or unsuitable, and for loading and stacking safely and within reasonable weight limits.</p>

      <h2>7. Indemnification</h2>
      <p>You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Black Swamp Totes and its owners and employees from any claims, damages, losses, liabilities, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys’ fees) arising from your use of the bins or equipment, your violation of this Agreement, or your violation of any law or any third party’s rights.</p>

      <h2>8. Payment authorization</h2>
      <p>You authorize Black Swamp Totes to charge the payment method on file for extension fees, late fees, cleaning fees, replacement costs for lost or damaged bins, and any other charges arising under this Agreement. Where a refundable security deposit applies, we may apply it toward these amounts and charge any excess to the card on file. You will receive an itemized summary of any such charges.</p>

      <h2>9. Cancellation</h2>
      <p>Cancellations 48 or more hours before the scheduled delivery receive a full refund of the rental balance; cancellations within 48 hours (rental not started) receive a 50% refund; no-shows and after the rental has started are non-refundable. Any refundable security deposit is returned in full on cancellation.</p>

      <h2>10. Governing law &amp; venue</h2>
      <p>This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of Ohio, without regard to conflict-of-laws rules. Any dispute shall be brought exclusively in the state or federal courts located in <strong>Lucas County, Ohio</strong>, and you consent to that venue and jurisdiction.</p>

      <h2>11. Electronic acceptance</h2>
      <p>By checking the “I have read and agree to the Rental Agreement and Liability Waiver” box at booking, you adopt that action as your electronic signature under the federal E-SIGN Act and the Ohio Uniform Electronic Transactions Act, and you consent to transact and receive records electronically. Depending on the equipment, you may also be asked to e-sign a rental agreement at checkout; both records govern your rental.</p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:<%= supportEmail %>"><%= supportEmail %></a> or call (419) 262-2837.</p>

      <p class="dim" style="margin-top:28px;font-size:13px;">Highlighted amounts above are placeholders for the business owner to fill in. This is starter language and is <strong>not legal advice</strong>; have an Ohio attorney review it before relying on it.</p>
    </article>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
